This paper is about Dialogue State Tracking (DST) which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and falls under the Computer Science category. The paper proposes a BERT-based model for DST which is a popular deep learning architecture used in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which covers NLP and speech processing. The paper also involves multi-task learning which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML), making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The proposed model is based on deep learning which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques such as querying dialogue history, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
